Overall Progress
Recall speed continues to improve, especially with practical travel, restaurant, and conversation phrases. Mixed review from previous weeks shows that long-term retention is improving rather than simply memorizing the newest lesson. The remaining weak points are mostly individual vocabulary words rather than sentence structure, indicating continued growth toward conversational fluency.

Tomorrow’s goal will be to complete a second review of Pimsleur Unit 3 Lesson 6, finish the remaining flashcards and challenge phrases, and continue reinforcing both new vocabulary and older conversational phrases through active recall.
